-- Philippine Stocks: Energy Development, Philex Mining, Union Bank
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m   a n d   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 2012-01-30T07:49:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/san-miguel-vista-land-lifescapes-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Philippine (PASHR)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon break in  Manila ,
unless stated otherwise.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  fell 0.8 percent to
4,644.49.  Energy Development Corp. (EDC)   slumped 10 percent to
5.66 pesos, its biggest decline since April 2009, after the
nation’s largest geothermal company said repair works at its
BacMan plant will be extended. First Gen Corp. (FGEN PM), Energy
Development’s parent, dropped 10 percent to 13 pesos.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)   dropped 1.8 percent to 269
pesos. The nation’s largest power distributor plans to invest
42.6 billion pesos (989 million) through 2014 even amid lower
distribution rates. It spent 33.8 billion pesos from 2008 to
2011, the company said in a disclosure to the stock exchange.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s largest metals
producer, lost 2.5 percent to 23 pesos, the biggest drop since
Dec. 15. Spot gold fell for the first time in four days,
dropping as much as 0.7 percent to $1,726.43 an ounce, while
copper futures on the London Metal Exchange declined as much as
1.8 percent to $8,370.75 a metric ton.  Union Bank of the Philippines  (UBP PM) gained 1.3 percent
to 74 pesos, a record high, after reporting profit last year
rose to 6.6 billion pesos ($153 million) from 5.35 billion pesos
in 2010.  To contact the reporters on this story:
